
Overview of noun criterion

The noun criterion has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (3) standard, criterion, measure, touchstone -- (a basis for comparison; a reference point against which other things can be evaluated; "the schools comply with federal standards"; "they set the measure for all subsequent work")
2. (2) criterion, standard -- (the ideal in terms of which something can be judged; "they live by the standards of their community")
